- Moony @ 4:18 AM PDT <br>
New Alternate Advancement skills are currently live on the test server only. These may or may not go live to all servers with the launch of the Planes of Power expansion. Below is the list thus far. Full details can be found here.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Planar Power<br>
This ability raises the maximum that your statistics can be raised to, with items or spells, by 5 points per rank. <br>
<br>
Planar Durability<br>
Each rank of this ability adds an additional 5% to your maximum hit points. <br>
<br>
Advanced Innate Strength<br>
This ability raises your innate Strength by two points per rank.<br>
<br>
<br>
Advanced Innate Stamina<br>
This ability raises your innate Stamina by two points per rank. <br>
<br>
Advanced Innate Agility<br>
This ability raises your innate Agility by two points per rank.<br>
<br>
Advanced Innate Dexterity<br>
This ability raises your innate Dexterity by two points per rank.<br>
<br>
Advanced Innate Intelligence<br>
This ability raises your innate Intelligence by two points per rank.<br>
<br>
Advanced Innate Wisdom<br>
This ability raises your innate Wisdom by two points per rank.<br>
<br>
Advanced Innate Charisma<br>
This ability raises your innate Charisma by two points per rank.<br>
<br>
Innate Enlightenment<br>
Each rank of this ability raises the maximum that you may raise your Intelligence and Wisdom by ten points.<br>
<br>
Marr's Protection<br>
This ability raises your base resistance to magic-based spells by two points per rank. <br>
<br>
Warding of Solusek<br>
This ability raises your base resistance to fire-based spells by two points per rank. <br>
<br>
Blessing of E'ci<br>
This ability raises your base resistance to cold-based spells by two points per rank. <br>
<br>
Shroud of The Faceless<br>
This ability raises your base resistance to poison-based spells by two points per rank. <br>
<br>
Bertoxxulous' Gift<br>
This ability raises your base resistance to disease-based spells by two points per rank. <br>
<br>
Advanced Spell Casting Mastery<br>
This ability increases the chance of making your specialization checks by five percent per rank. The effect reduces your chance to fizzle and increases your chance of using less mana when casting a spell. <br>
<br>
Advanced Healing Adept<br>
This ability increases the maximum effectiveness of your healing spells by five percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Advanced Healing Gift<br>
This ability increases your chance to score an exceptional heal by two percent per rank. An exceptional heal doubles the healing value of the spell. <br>
<br>
Hastened Divinity<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Bestow Divine Aura by ten percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Hastened Resurrection<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Divine Resurrection by ten percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Hastened Turning<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Turn Undead by ten percent per rank.<br>
<br>
Hastened Purification of the Soul<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Purify Soul by ten percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Hastened Gathering<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Gather Mana by ten percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Hastened Rabidity<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Rabid Bear by ten percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Hastened Exodus<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Exodus by ten percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Hastened Root<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Strong Root by ten percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Hastened Mending<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Mend Companion by ten percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Hastened Banishment<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Turn Summoned by ten percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Hastened Call of the Dead<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Call to Corpse by ten percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Hastened Sleep of the Dead<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Dead Mesmerization by ten percent per rank.<br>
<br>
Elemental Translocation<br>
No information provided.<br>
<br>
Hastened Instigation<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Area Taunt by ten percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Furious Rampage<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Rampage by ten percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Hastened Purification of the Body<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Purify Body by ten percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Hasty Exit<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Escape by ten percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Hastened Purification<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Purge Poison by ten percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Coup de Grace<br>
This ability gives you a chance to immediately slay an NPC that is below ten percent health and fleeing with a single, well placed strike. The first level works on NPC's below level 55, the second on NPC's below 57, and the third on NPC's below 59. <br>
<br>
Fury of the Ages<br>
This ability further increases your chance to score a critical blow against your opponent. <br>
<br>
Flash of Steel<br>
This ability further increases your chance of doubly riposting your opponent each time you score a successful riposte by ten percent per rank. <br>
<br>
Mastery of the Past<br>
This ability makes it impossible for you to fizzle a spell. The first level affects all spells below level 54. The second, on all spells below level 56. The third, on all spells below level 58. <br>
<br>
Suspended Minion<br>
This ability grants the summoner the ability to suspend and recall their existing pet at will. The first rank suspends the pet at its current health only, while the second rank suspends the pet with all of its beneficial effects as well as its weapons and armor.<br>
<br>
Spirit Call<br>
This ability calls a number of spirit companions into existence directed at a target. The companions attack the target without question until they are called back to their home plane 60 seconds later. The initial rank of this ability calls three companions. Additional ranks add one companion each. <br>
<br>
Celestial Renewal<br>
This ability grants improvements to your existing Celestial Regeneration. <br>
<br>
Allegiant Familiar<br>
This ability will cause your existing Improved Familiar to summon an even more powerful companion. This familiar provides even greater benefits to its owner than its predecessor.<br>
<br>
Hand of Piety<br>
This ability invokes the direct blessing of your deity upon all of those nearby. All in range are healed 750 hit points in the first rank, and successive ranks each add 250. <br>
<br>
Lightning Reflexes<br>
This ability further increases your chance of completely avoiding incoming melee damage. <br>
<br>
Innate Defense<br>
This ability further increases your mitigation of incoming melee damage. <br>
<br>
Mithaniel's Binding<br>
This ability further increases the amount of healing provided by a single bandage while binding wounds. <br>
<br>
Mending of the Tranquil<br>
This ability further increases the chance of performing a superior mend. <br>
<br>
Raging Flurry<br>
This ability further increases the chance of performing a flurry attack upon successfully scoring a triple attack. <br>
<br>
Guardian of the Forest<br>
This ability transforms you into an exceptionally bloodthirsty wolf that attacks with lightning speed, for a brief time.<br>
<br>
Spirit of the Wood<br>
For a brief time, you are able to commune with the woodland spirits who provide you r party with exceptional regenerative abilities and a protective shield of armor and thorns. <br>
<br>
Bestial Frenzy<br>
This ability grants you a chance of performing a double attack in any given combat round. <br>
<br>
Harmonious Attack<br>
This ability grants you a chance of performing a double attack in any given combat round. <br>
<br>
Knight's Advantage<br>
This ability grants you an increased chance of performing a double attack with two-handed weapons in any given combat round. <br>
<br>
Ferocity<br>
This ability grants you an increased chance of performing a double attack in any given combat round. <br>
<br>
Animation Empathy<br>
Progressive ranks of this ability grant you finer control over your animations. At its initial level, you are allowed to give your animations ‘guard’ and ‘follow’ commands. At the second ank, ‘attack’ commands. At the final rank, ‘back off’ commands. <br>
<br>
Unfailing Divinity<br>
The most devout find that their calls are answered with much greater frequency. This ability grants your Death Pact-type spells a second chance to successfully heal their target. Additional ranks of this ability cause said spells to do a portion of their healing value even on a complete failure. <br>
<br>
Resonant Warcry<br>
This ability significantly improves the duration of your Warcry and lessens the time required between uses. <br>
<br>
Viscid Roots<br>
Root spells applied by the owner of this ability are significantly less likely to break when the victim takes damage initiated by anyone, unlike previous abilities which only affect damage caused by the caster.<br>
<br>
Sionachie’s Crescendo<br>
This ability provides an even greater extension to the range of group songs. <br>
<br>
Ayonae’s Tutelage<br>
This ability allows for further improvements in the use of all instrument types. <br>
<br>
Rizlona’s Chorus<br>
This ability allows for further specialization and improved use of your voice. <br>
<br>
Rush to Judgment<br>
Training in this ability shortens the time between uses of Divine Stun by seven seconds per rank. <br>
<br>
Feigned Minion<br>
This ability allows you to instruct your pet to feign death via the '/pet feign' command. Three ranks of this skill are available, causing your pet to succeed 25%, 50%, and 75% of the time, respectively. <br>
<br>
Boastful Bellow<br>
This ability allows you to bellow with a force that causes physical harm to your enemies as well as potentially interfering with their spell casting.<br>
<br>
Vanishing Blade<br>
The ability allows you to strike your opponents with such speed that they are frequently left dumbfounded, not entirely certain of where the blow originated. <br>
<br>
Fervent Blessing<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Lay Hands by twelve minutes per rank.<br>
<br>
Touch of the Wicked<br>
This ability decreases the amount of time required between uses of Harm Touch and its upgrades by twelve minutes per rank.<br>
<br>
Unstoppable Force<br>
This ability grants you the chance to score an additional attack with two-handed weapons. <br>
<br>
Speed of the Knight<br>
This ability grants you the chance to score an additional attack with two-handed weapons. <br>
<br>
Shroud of Stealth<br>
This ability provides a previously unheard of level of stealth. The Rogue is able to draw shadows about himself so completely, even creatures that are normally not fooled by such trickery are frequently unable to see him. <br>
<br>
Nimble Evasion<br>
This ability grants you a chance to hide or evade while moving. Each rank provides an increasing chance. <br>
<br>
Technique of Master Wu<br>
Under the tutelage of Wu, Monks are able to hone their skills to the point of being able to execute a second and sometimes even third strike when scoring a hit with their special attacks. This ability grants a ten percent increase in the chance of scoring multiple special attacks, per rank.<br>
<br>
Host of the Elements<br>
This ability calls an assault of elemental minions into existence directed at a target. The minions attack the target without question until they are called back to their plane 60 seconds later. The initial rank of this ability calls five elementals. Additional ranks add two elementals each. <br>
<br>
Hobble of Spirits<br>
This advancement gives you the ability to imbue your pet with an attack that is reputed to slow its enemies' movements.<br>
<br>
Frenzy of Spirit<br>
This ability gives Beastlords the power to send themselves into an animalistic frenzy, bent only on slaughter, for a brief period of time.<br>
<br>
Paragon of Spirit<br>
This ability allows the Beastlord to share some of his natural attunement with his party in the form of health and mana.<br>
<br>
Radiant Cure<br>
This ability grants its wielder the ability to cure their party of many afflictions, poisons, curses, and harmful magics. <br>
<br>
Hastened Stealth<br>
This ability reduces the time between which you may attempt to hide or evade by one second per rank. <br>
<br>
Divine Arbitration<br>
Using this ability balances the health of your group such that all group members end up with the same amount of damage taken. The first rank does so at a 20 percent penalty to the average, the second rank does to at a 10 percent penalty, and the final rank does so at no penalty. <br>
<br>
Wrath of the Wild<br>
Developed by the denizens of Tranquility as a deterrent to potential <br>
attackers, this ability will shield you with a single-hit, large damage barrier of thorns. Additional ranks of this ability increase the amount of damage that is inflicted. <br>
<br>
Virulent Paralysis<br>
This ability causes your target to succumb to a sudden, violent attack, after which they are frequently unable to move for a time. Each rank of this ability increases the amount of time that the victim remains immobile. <br>
<br>
Harvest of the Mind<br>
This ability gathers streams of additional mana into your being. <br>
Servant of Ro<br>
This ability calls a loyal servant into being who will repeatedly hurl fire at your target. Each rank of this ability increases the amount of time that the servant is able to remain by your side (45, 70, and 90 seconds). <br>
<br>
Eldritch Rune<br>
This ability provides Enchanters with an additional line of defense in the form of an added self-only rune. Each rank of this ability provides a stronger rune than the previous. <br>
<br>
Wake the Dead<br>
This ability calls the shade of a nearby corpse back to life to serve the Necromancer. The soulless abomination will fight the target, until called back to the afterlife some time later. The slave summoned by the first rank of this ability serves for 60 seconds, and each increasing rank adds 15 additional seconds. <br>
